On the one-year anniversary of the Parkland shooting, President Trump issued a statement honoring the memory of the 17 victims and recommitting to ensuring the safety of all Americans, especially children. He highlighted the actions taken by his administration, such as signing the STOP School Violence Act and Fix NICS Act into law, expanding health and other services to low-income schools, and banning bump stocks. The Federal Commission on School Safety also released a report with nearly 100 policy recommendations. The President expressed solidarity with the Parkland community and emphasized the need for collaboration between educational personnel, law enforcement, and local leadership to prevent acts of violence in schools. Melania and the President offered prayers for healing and vowed to continue working towards secure schools and safe communities.